(1) The law of the German Democratic Republic continues to apply in accordance with this article, insofar as it does not contradict this constitution.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(2) The rights pursuant to Articles 8 paragraph 2, 21 paragraph 4, 23 paragraph 3, 26 and 27 paragraph 3 sentence 4 shall only exist until the applicable law is adapted to this constitution to the extent that it exists at the time of its entry into force; the adjustment must be completed by December 31, 1990 at the latest.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(3) Installations that contravene the provisions of Article 33Paragraphs 2 and 3 cause hazards or impairments to the natural environment can continue to be operated for five years from the entry into force of this constitution, provided they do not exceed the level of the emissions caused by them on March 31, 1990 and immediately take effective measures to gradually reduce them the limits allowed by this constitution are taken. The provisions of Article 33 paragraph 4 apply to contaminated sites only in accordance with the law.}
