\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(1) The land reform and the deprivation of property, which have been confirmed by Article 24 of the Constitution of the German Democratic Republic of October 7, 1949 , are inviolable.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(2) Expropriations and other forms of deprivation of property that took place at the time of their execution in accordance with the law of the German Democratic Republic remain effective regardless of formal inaccuracies in land registers, cadastral registers and other public registers. The same applies to property rights that citizens have left behind after leaving the German Democratic Republic and which have been finally transferred to third parties or are being used by third parties in accordance with the applicable law of the German Democratic Republic. Usages of such property rights are to be protected. The users have the right to purchase property after the on 31. December 1989 applicable legislation on valuation, insofar as the property is in the hands of a public authority. As far as apartments, residential properties and properties used for recreational purposes are affected, the personal users have this right.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(3) Property that has been confiscated in violation of the applicable law of the German Democratic Republic is to be returned to the rightful owner upon request, provided that it is still at the disposal of a public authority. This does not apply to apartments and residential properties as well as properties used for recreational purposes. It also does not apply to property that has passed into the disposal of cooperatives and state-owned companies.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(4) If a reimbursement according to paragraph 3 is excluded, the dispositions made in the meantime remain effective. The legal status of the users is determined in accordance with paragraph 2 sentences 3 to 5. Usages are to be protected even if a reimbursement takes place in accordance with paragraph 3. Compensation is payable to the previous owners. The compensation is to be determined on a legal basis, taking fair consideration of the interests of the general public and those involved on the basis of the valuation law applicable at the time of leaving the German Democratic Republic; in doing so, the time and the special personal circumstances that led to leaving the German Democratic Republic must be taken into account. The compensation can be paid in installments. Compensation is excluded in the case of burden compensation payments with regard to the loss of property. In appropriate cases, an amicable balance of interests between the parties involved, which takes the place of compensation payments, is to be promoted.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(5) The full ownership rights to movable property, which were in the fiduciary administration of the state or another trustee according to the legal provisions in force until December 31, 1989, are to be restored at the request of the entitled persons; as far as the trustee has this, the proceeds are to be handed over. This does not apply to movable property that is used by state-owned companies or cooperatives.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(6) Insofar as ownership of immovable property held in trust is not transferred to new legal entities in accordance with the following provisions, the full property rights of the entitled persons must be restored upon their request. The ownership of flats, residential properties and properties used for recreational purposes in a trust is transferred to the holders of communal autonomy in whose territory they are located. The provisions of paragraph 2 sentences 3 and 4 apply to personal users. Ownership of immovable cooperative assets held in trust is transferred to the cooperative using them. Title to immovable business assets held in trust shall pass to the trustee. It is to be transferred to the companies using it as soon as they take on the legal form of an independent company. These companies are owned by the country in which they are based. The provisions of paragraph 4 sentences 4 to 8 apply.}
