\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(2) To be effective, the agreement requires the approval of two thirds of the members of the People's Chamber and confirmation in a referendum.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(3) This agreement is intended to contain provisions on the accelerated adjustment of the economic power of the parts of the country located on the current territory of the German Democratic Republic and the living conditions of their residents to the conditions existing in the current territory of the Federal Republic of Germany. In order to realize the right of the citizens of the German Democratic Republic to participate in the democratic self-determination of the German people, efforts must be made to hold an all-German constituent assembly.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(4) The agreement should also provide that the human and civil rights guaranteed in this constitution continue to apply on the current territory of the German Democratic Republic even if they establish rights that are not contained in the Basic Law. This also applies to the direct binding of third parties to these rights. They should continue to apply as state constitutional law; the application of Article 31 of the Basic Law for the Federal Republic of Germany is to be excluded in this respect. The agreement should provide that legal provisions of the German Democratic Republic, which are compatible with the aforementioned rights, but not with the Basic Law for the Federal Republic of Germany, notwithstanding Article 31 of the Basic Law for the Federal Republic of Germany, continue to apply as state law on the current territory of the German Democratic Republic. Changes to the law that continues to apply in accordance with this paragraph require the consent of all the states established on the current territory of the German Democratic Republic.}
